tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, suggesting impaired glucose metabolism or early diabetes, despite normal fasting glucose. Creatinine is slightly elevated, which may indicate reduced kidney function and warrants further assessment. All other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend follow-up for glycemic control and renal function.
